    <section id="history">
        <h3>Historical High Not<span style="font-weight:bold;color:#333;background-color:yellow;">ES</span></h3>
        <ul>
            <li class="fragment">Netscape and Sun employ Brendan Eich to create a scripting language to interface with Java (1995)</li>
            <li class="fragment">In about 2 weeks, Eich created <i style="color:yellow;">mocha</i></li>
            <li class="fragment">™ issues with "mocha" ― re-branded as <i style="color:yellow;">LiveScript</i></li>
            <li class="fragment">Popularity of Java ― re-branded as <i style="color:yellow;">JavaScript</i></li>
            <li class="fragment">Netscape asked <a href="https://www.ecma-international.org/default.htm">Ecma</a> to maintain ISO standard (1996)</li>
            <li class="fragment"><a href="http://tmsearch.uspto.gov/bin/showfield?f=doc&state=4804:dy5avd.2.4">Oracle owned JavaScript™</a> ― maintained as <i style="color:yellow;">ECMAScript</i> (1997)</li>
            <li class="fragment">Specification, <a href="https://www.ecma-international.org/publications/standards/Ecma-262.htm">ECMA-262</a>, maintained by <a href="https://www.ecma-international.org/memento/TC39-M.htm">TC39</a></li>
        </ul>
    </section>
    <section id="release-history">
