        <ul>
            <li class="fragment"><span style="font-family:courier;font-weight:bold;">1997</span> ― ES1 published</li>
            <li class="fragment"><span style="font-family:courier;font-weight:bold;">1998</span> ― ES2 published</li>
            <li class="fragment"><span style="font-family:courier;font-weight:bold;">2002</span> ― ES3 published</li>
            <li class="fragment" style="color:yellow;">JavaScript (ECMAScript) gets famous</li>
            <li class="fragment" style="color:red;">ES4 skipped because of reasons</li>
            <li class="fragment"><span style="font-family:courier;font-weight:bold;">2011</span> ― ES5 published</li>
            <li class="fragment"><span style="font-family:courier;font-weight:bold;">2015</span> ― ES6 published</li>
            <li class="fragment" style="color:yellow;">TC39 transitions to yearly release schedule</li>
            <li class="fragment"><span style="font-family:courier;font-weight:bold;">2016</span> ― ES7 (ES2016) published</li></li>
            <li class="fragment"><span style="font-family:courier;font-weight:bold;">2017</span> ― ES8 (ES2017) published in June</li></li>
        </ul>
